post_text:
Senior Parents,
I know this is super short notice, but our Chromebooks are ready to be issued to the senior class beginning tomorrow. Please be sure to have their usage agreement form filled out and on file. We will also be accepting their usage fee of $20 at that time. If they do not have the money, they will still be issued the Chromebook, but they will need to turn in that usage fee shortly after. We are very excited about the devices we are putting in the hands of our students and appreciate the Rogers ISD School Board for their support. WAR!!!

post_text:
Our amazing maintenance crew has been hard at work getting Merk Field ready for the big game tonight. A special thank you to the City of Rogers for letting us borrow bleachers from the little league fields. We have added 12 sets of portable bleachers to increase our capacity. We have also moved both bands behind each goalposts to allow more fans in the bleachers on both sides. We will have some home side tickets available tonight on a first come basis. All tickets are $4. Academy tickets are being sold at Academy ISD. There will be no visitor tickets sold at the gate. Masks must be worn while coming into the stadium and when not social distanced (per UIL guidelines). No Re-entry. Anyone not able to attend in person can catch the game on Schoolboy Sports, Rogers’s new live streaming camera- www.nfhsnetwork.com (search Rogers High School - subscription required) and also on KWTX- CW channel.

LET’S PLAY SOME FOOTBALL!!!

post_text:
Rogers ISD is accepting transfer applications for the 2020-21 school year. Rogers ISD does not charge a transfer fee. We determine eligibility by checking the student's attendance history, discipline history, and academic history. Class size limits could also be a factor at certain grade levels. More information can be found on the website www.rogersisd.org under the Parents dropdown menu.

Rogers ISD is a Texas Education Agency A-Rated District (2018-19) that has a PreK-12 enrollment of around 850 students. Transfer applications can be picked up at the administration building M-Th from 7:30 - 4:00. If you are looking for a small school atmosphere for your student, but you don't live in our district boundaries, transferring might be an option.

post_text:
Merk Field is ready for Graduation tonight at 8:30. Gates will open at 7:30 for invited guests. Here are a couple of reminders:
1. If you have symptoms, stay home and watch on Facebook Live (we will go live at 8:15)
2. Please wear a face mask as a sign of respect to others
3. If you will be sitting on the field, bring your chair. (Wagons will be allowed to transport chairs)
4. You MUST enter with your entire group. If you are sitting on the field, enter through visitor’s side gate, if sitting in the bleachers, enter on home side.
5. Please practice social distancing while entering, during the ceremony, and exiting the stadium
6. REMEMBER: we have done our best to make this event memorable for our Seniors. Much of this was pulled together in the past 10 days. It may not be perfect, but we have tried our best.

W.A.R.

Rogers ISD is participating in the State-Wide campaign to keep everyone healthy!

1. Proof of Residency (copy of current water bill, electric bill, or lease)
2. Current Copy of Driver's License
3. Copy of Original Birth Certificate
4. Social Security Card (of the Student)
5. Current Shot Record

Attention: former Rogers ISD top 10% graduates. There is a movement by some lawmakers to do away with the top 10% automatic qualifier rule in next year's legislature.

However, some state lawmakers are wanting to make sure the laws stays as it is and are calling schools asking for stories of students who have taken advantage of the top 10% rule to help them get into a university they may not have without the rule.

Thank you for all of your support over the past couple of weeks while students at the elementary, middle school and high school took their STAAR tests. Unfortunately, the results will not be available until after we are out of school for the summer.

post_text:
Parents,
Today around 2:00 pm, I received a report from our Middle School Principal there was a fire in the downstairs boys' restroom at the middle school. A student had gone to the restroom and reported the fire to a teacher, whose classroom is right beside the restroom. The teacher accessed the situation and quickly grabbed a fire extinguisher and put out the fire, which turned out to be the toilet paper roll. Through investigation, the Principal was able to determine which student had been in the restroom prior to the student who reported it. We will follow the Rogers ISD Student Code of Conduct in dealing with the student discipline. There were no students or staff injured and property damage will be assessed soon. Thanks to an aware student and a quick-thinking teacher, a potentially more serious situation was avoided.

Joe Craig
Superintendent

post_text:
Parents,

We want to make you aware that on our middle school GT field trip today to Austin, our bus was involved in a very minor collision. While driving down the highway, another vehicle drifted toward our bus and side-swiped the bus. The other vehicle then pulled away and left, without us being able to get a license plate. The were no injuries to the driver or any of the students or teacher. The bus has a little paint on it from the other vehicle, but no damage that would affect its safety or drivability. We reported the situation to law enforcement and continued on with the field trip. We want to be proactive in reporting the situation to parents, so rumors don’t turn it into something more than it actually was.

Joe Craig
Superintendent
Rogers ISD

***Please Share with Parents of Transfer Students or Potential Transfers***

Applications for NEW Transfers for the 2018-19 will be available on Monday , April 2nd. Parents will need to come by the administration office to pick up a transfer packet. Our office hours are 7:30-4:00. Rogers ISD does not charge a transfer fee, but does look at attendance and discipline history of each student applying. Class size (students:teacher ratio) also can be a factor in the final decision.

If you are a current transfer, the transfer renewal information will be mailed to you the first week of April.

If you have any questions about the transfer process, please call the administration office at 254-642-3802.

Dear Parents:

It is now Flu Season and we need your help. If your child has a fever, please do not give them Tylenol or Motrin and send them to school. Please keep your child at home until he/she has been fever free for 24 hours without Tylenol or Motrin. Please remember that hand washing with soap and water is essential in keeping down the spread of germs. Please use hand sanitizer when soap and water are not available. If you have any questions please feel free to contact the Nursing Staff at Rogers ISD 642-7074; 642-7075 with any questions. Have a great long weekend and we will see your children next Thursday.

post_text: Rogers ISD would like to thank KCEN TV Channel 6 for extending the invitation to shoot live at Merk Field as part of their Channel 6 Spirit Stick series. post_text:
Rogers ISD is starting an after-school program for Elementary Students. This came about as a result of parent surveys that were sent out last month showing a need for this type of program. Our goal is to start the program in October if we have enough students sign up. We need at least 17 students to make it viable. Cost is $100 per month / per student and will include an afternoon snack (this is virtually the same price as the after-school program at Ralph Wilson). The program will run until 6:00 pm Monday-Friday. Students will have snack time, homework/academic time, and play time.

If you are interested in signing up, a link is on the Rogers ISD website. You can contact the administration office if you have any questions.

In an effort to celebrate the positive things going on at Rogers ISD, we want to brag on our teachers and students whose STAAR scores last year were at 90% or at least 10 points above the state average. If you see one of these teachers or students who were in these grades / subjects, tell them "Great Job"

5th Grade Math - 97% (16 pts above state avg)
5th Grade Reading - 90% - (19 pts above state avg)
6th Grade Reading - 83% - (16 pts above state avg)
7th Grade Reading - 85% - (13 pts above state avg)
7th Grade Writing - 79% - (11 pts above state avg)
8th Grade Reading - 88% - (12 pts above state avg)
U.S. History - 96% - (4 pts above state avg)

We had several other grades / subjects VERY close to these goals. We expect many more next year. Keep up the GREAT WORK Teachers & Students. You make Rogers ISD Proud!

post_text:
In an effort to help our community, the Rogers CYC (community wide Christian Youth Club) group is organizing an event where people can donate any clothes / shoes that your kids have outgrown or don't wear anymore and then we will make these items available to families that may need them. First Baptist Rogers has graciously donated their facility to host the event. Drop off for donated items will be THIS Friday (August 11) from 2:00 - 4:00 pm at the fellowship hall. The items will be for sale ($.25 - $1.00) on Saturday from 8:30 - 11:00 am at the fellowship hall. Any items not sold will be donated to other local organizations. If your kids have outgrown their last year's clothes, they may be able to fit someone else. When Eagles help Eagles.....Everyone wins! The proceeds will help fund the CYC Wednesday after school program, which last year served about 50 kids per week at NO COST to them.

Please share this post so we can get the word out about this event. It's a short turnaround this year, but hopefully we can make it an annual event.

The proceeds will help fund the CYC Wednesday after school program, which last year served about 50 kids per week at NO COST to them.

Please share this post so we can get the word out about this event. It's a short turnaround this year, but hopefully we can make it an annual event.

post_text:
Rogers ISD is accepting transfer applications for students going into 6th grade through High School. As of the end of the 2016-17 School Year, Rogers ISD had 856 students PreK-12th. We expect to have about 200 students in our middle school for 2017-18, and about 280 in our high school. As a small school, Rogers typically offers smaller class sizes and a great family atmosphere for students. Extra-curricular participation is encouraged for all students, and traditionally Rogers ISD has been an area leader in boys and girls athletics, academic UIL, One Act Play, Ag Science, and Band. We have students who participate in Texas Bioscience Institute and Dual Credit at Temple College. Rogers ISD provides transportation to students attending these programs. Rogers ISD DOES NOT charge a transfer fee, but students applying for transfer must meet attendance and discipline requirements.

Those interested in applying for transfer can come to the Rogers ISD administration building to fill out the transfer paperwork. New student registration begins on August,4.
